Message: Not at all, it's just that people taught English as a second language are taught a fixed idea of what English was at a certain point of time, whereas native speakers are constantly evolving the language, sorting out which things are most fit to survive and discarding those that are useless or no longer needed.

So some people might think the distinction between less and fewer is important and should be upheld, but as that distinction becomes fewer of a thing that people need, the number of people who hold that view will become less.
